glosses: to kick, especially for an animal
to decline, turn down, reject (something); to throw away (an opportunity, a chance)
to tuck something into a hole
(for a cow) to not give milk
to clean off feather or hair by beating them

etymology: From Ottoman Turkish تپمك (tepmek, “to kick, dance”), دپمك (depmek), from Old Anatolian Turkish دپمك (depmek), from Proto-Turkic *tep-. Related to Old Turkic [script needed] (tep-, “to hit, kick”).
